### Connection Handling
```rust
async fn accept_loop(listener: UnixListener, daemon: Arc<Mutex<ModelDaemon>>) {
    loop {
        tokio::select! {
            Ok((stream, _)) = listener.accept() => {
                let daemon = Arc::clone(&daemon);
                tokio::spawn(async move {
                    handle_connection(stream, daemon).await;
                });
            }
            _ = idle_timeout_check(&daemon) => {
                info!("Idle timeout reached, shutting down");
                break;
            }
        }
    }
    cleanup(&daemon).await;
}

async fn handle_connection(mut stream: UnixStream, daemon: Arc<Mutex<ModelDaemon>>) {
    // Read length-prefixed MessagePack envelope
    let len = stream.read_u32().await?;
    let mut buf = vec![0u8; len as usize];
    stream.read_exact(&mut buf).await?;

    let envelope: Envelope = rmp_serde::from_slice(&buf)?;
    assert_eq!(envelope.version, 1, "Unsupported protocol version");

    let request: Request = rmp_serde::from_slice(&envelope.payload)?;
    let response = daemon.lock().await.handle_request(request).await;

    // Write response
    let resp_bytes = rmp_serde::to_vec(&response)?;
    let resp_envelope = Envelope { version: 1, id: envelope.id, payload: resp_bytes };
    let envelope_bytes = rmp_serde::to_vec(&resp_envelope)?;
    stream.write_u32(envelope_bytes.len() as u32).await?;
    stream.write_all(&envelope_bytes).await?;
}
```

### Idle Timeout
- Timer resets on every request
- Default: 30 minutes (configurable in daemon.toml)
- On timeout: log, unload models, remove socket + PID file, exit
- SIGTERM/SIGINT: same graceful shutdown path

### Socket Permissions
- Socket created with mode 0600 (owner-only)
- PID file: 0644

### Startup Sequence
1. Parse config from ~/.config/xf/daemon.toml
2. Apply nice/ionice/resource limits (bd-ld7m)
3. Bind UDS at /tmp/xf-daemon-{uid}.sock
4. Write PID to /tmp/xf-daemon-{uid}.pid
5. Install signal handlers (SIGTERM, SIGINT)
6. Enter accept loop
7. Log: "Daemon ready, PID={pid}, socket={path}"

