 {"id":"bd-21lt","title":"Task: Daemon service integration (systemd/launchd)","description":"## Task: Daemon Service Integration (systemd/launchd)

Provide optional service definitions so users can keep the model daemon warm across sessions, with proper health checks, logging, restart policies, and environment configuration.

## Priority: P2
This is nice-to-have after the core daemon works. Users can always run `xf daemon start` manually.

## Deliverables

### 1. systemd Unit File (`scripts/daemon/xf-daemon.service`)
```ini
[Unit]
Description=xf Warm Model Daemon
Documentation=man:xf(1)
After=network.target
StartLimitIntervalSec=300
StartLimitBurst=5

[Service]
Type=notify
ExecStart=/usr/local/bin/xf daemon start --foreground --systemd
ExecStop=/usr/local/bin/xf daemon stop
ExecReload=/bin/kill -HUP $MAINPID

# Resource management
Nice=10
IOSchedulingClass=idle
IOSchedulingPriority=7
MemoryMax=2G
MemoryHigh=1536M
CPUQuota=200%

# Security hardening
NoNewPrivileges=true
ProtectSystem=strict
ProtectHome=read-only
PrivateTmp=true
ReadWritePaths=/tmp/xf-daemon.sock
ReadWritePaths=%h/.cache/xf

# Restart policy
Restart=on-failure
RestartSec=5
WatchdogSec=60

# Logging
StandardOutput=journal
StandardError=journal
SyslogIdentifier=xf-daemon

# Environment
Environment=XF_DAEMON_SOCKET=/tmp/xf-daemon.sock
Environment=XF_MODEL_CACHE=%h/.cache/xf/models
Environment=RUST_LOG=xf_daemon=info
EnvironmentFile=-%h/.config/xf/daemon.env

[Install]
WantedBy=default.target
```

### 2. systemd User Install Script
```bash
#!/bin/bash
# scripts/daemon/install-systemd.sh
set -euo pipefail

SERVICE_NAME="xf-daemon"
USER_UNIT_DIR="${XDG_CONFIG_HOME:-$HOME/.config}/systemd/user"

echo "Installing xf-daemon systemd user service..."

mkdir -p "$USER_UNIT_DIR"
cp "$(dirname "$0")/xf-daemon.service" "$USER_UNIT_DIR/"

# Substitute home directory
sed -i "s|%h|$HOME|g" "$USER_UNIT_DIR/xf-daemon.service"

systemctl --user daemon-reload
echo "Service installed. Usage:"
echo "  systemctl --user enable xf-daemon   # Start on login"
echo "  systemctl --user start xf-daemon    # Start now"
echo "  systemctl --user status xf-daemon   # Check status"
echo "  journalctl --user -u xf-daemon -f   # Follow logs"
```

